bug.short_desc: IE7 selects text when resizing of dragging windows

long_desc.thetext: When dragging or resizing a qx.ui.window.Window in IE7 the text (labels, check box labels, etc) of underlying windows get selected.
Created attachment 107 Resizing a window selects underlying text in IE7
Created attachment 108 Draging a window in IE7 selects text of underlying windows
Seems to be true for IE6, too. The selection seems not to be permanent. It just seems to get temporary selecting while dragging around.

The problem in IE generally is that the proprietary attribute "unselectable" only works when the selection process was started on exactly the disabled element. It does not work if the selection starts from a selectable element. The way it was solved in SVN is to add a preventDefault to the mousemove event of the window handler. Maybe we found a better more generic way to fix the buggy IE in the future.
Fixed with r6710 and r6711

Just to be sure I fully understood: The problem could be solved when I would set the "unselectable" attribute for all draggable widgets. And this could be done from within my code i.e. calling setHtmlAttribute()?
